I think that I would decide to exclude immigrants from coming here based on personal characteristics as opposed to where they come from. However on the other side of the coin our nursing and care homes run on foreign nationalities as do our hospitals so I do not know the answer as we rely so much on these people working for us. Farmers will be in dire straits as well due to lack of workers when harvest is needed.. I do not think Britain is seen now as such a good country to visit. It is all such a shame and I along with politicians and other ordinary people do not seem to have any solutions.

Really interesting survey. For reference, my understanding of the economic impact of migration is based on the UCL surveys that include family costs on service, jail costs and projections for later life NHS. I also include my understanding from official government studies that show mass migration has a 2 to 3% negative impact on wages for unskilled labour.

Additionally, I factor in the 21% cost of immigration on house prices - I'm a buyer, not a seller so it's a negative impact for me as I find it harder to buy a house. Additionally, I believe that 21% is national, not London based which disproportionately receives immigration.
